1. First understand the basic workflow of github action stucture
name: First Workflow

on:
  push:

jobs:
  build_stage:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Print message
        run: echo "build stage is running"  // this is refer as step and inside step we are having multiple command to run . execute shell command inside runner
        

  test_stage:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Print message
        run: echo "test stage is running"


2. now we will understand the dependency of stage  by using needs keyword

3. i have noticed that piplined failed because of wrong key word and we use need keyword in test stage and test stage will only run if build stage has passed sucessfuly but here build stage fails so test stage has not started .. now i comment out the need part and run the pipeline then i saw build was fail because of wrong cmd but test stage has successfuly run ...

4. need keyword - > mainly create the pipeline order.


--> PLUGIN

5.  we can say if we want to use any plugin that time we will use "uses" keyword . 

6. actions/checkout@v4 this is one of the plugin that help us to checkout to github repo without this plugin github action can not able to access the code.

--> SET UP ENVIRONMENT 

uses:
↓
Which reusable action/plugin should run

with:
↓
What settings/inputs should be given to that action

- uses: actions/setup-node@v4

GitHub understands:

"Okay, use setup-node action"

But it doesn't know:

Node 18?
Node 20?
Node 22?

So we provide configuration:

with:
  node-version: 22

Another example:
- uses: actions/checkout@v4
  with:
    fetch-depth: 1

Use checkout action
with configuration:
fetch only limited git history
  